#Repost @natgeo ・・・ Photo by @FransLanting This is Mike a young male chimp we got to know in the Fongoli region of southeast Senegal. We worked with him and his family for six weeks following them on foot through their forest. There are less than 200 chimps left in Senegal and their future hangs in the balance just like it does for all chimps in Africa. Habitat loss and the bushmeat trade are the major threats to their survival. As we gather together with our own families during this holiday season let’s not forget our extended family on the great tree of life. We can all help chimps survive by supporting the individuals and the organizations that protect them and the forests they depend on. Check the links below for the World Wildlife Fund Conservation International Jane Goodall’s Roots and Shoots and @NatGeo Explorer Jill Pruetz’s Neighbor Ape project in Senegal which we support through GlobalGiving.org online. Follow me @FransLanting for more images and stories from our family tree. @janegoodallinst @world_wildlife @conservationorg #chimps #Africa #Senegal #wildlife #endangered #racingextinction #conservation

I had the opportunity to be 1 of 350 Division I II and III Athletes selected  to attend the 2017 NCAA Student Athlete Leadership Conference this past weekend. What an incredible experience! From daily seminars  about ways to combat the stigma of mental health and growth vs fixed mindsets to the guest speakers group work and community service to help the homeless and fostering of real genuine and authentic relationships I can look back over the past couple days and feel I have really learned how to effectively lead in any field that I am apart of. Thank you @cgpac12 for mentoring and helping each and everyone of us. Also having the opportunity along with @winwithkins to represent the entire @accsports conference and @uva_track was incredible!  I can’t wait to see what the future holds for each and everyone of us #LearnLead #growthmindset #ncaa #blessed #beyond #measure

I am happy to announce along with @jade_briana and @miabarron I will be launching a television show called THE HOO encompassing all UVA track and field and cross country on both the men's and women's teams. Along with meeting the teams you will get a more indepth look into the lives of our coaching staff the day in the life of a student athlete and recaps and previews of meets throughout the year.  I want to thank @coachfetz along with Stephanie Whitley for all your support with getting the show started and I am extremely excited to see what happens going forward. I also want to thank the Virginia Sports Video Services Department for getting myself and @jade_briana ingrained in producing The HOO. Lastly thank you to all of my friends family and mentors in the broadcasting realm who have helped me and inspired me in a variety of different ways and have helped me with  the little details while being a resource for me to pick their brains and learn something new each and everyday. 📍📍🛑🛑Also: Please come out and support the @uvacrosscountry team as they compete at Panorama Farms at 10AM EST! 👈🏽 I look forward to seeing you all there!! GO HOOS #uvatrackandfield #uvacrosscountry #THEHOO #hoostogether

ND Alum Claire Troia studied abroad at UCD in Fall of 2014. In the summer of 2017 she returned to Ireland to do work with a doctor in Dublin and through that connection presented at a conference in Croke Park this October in front of many esteemed doctors and researchers. We were so happy to spend time with Claire while she was in town for the conference and send her many well wishes as she continues on with her bright future!  The title of her paper:  Follow Up: Children with Retinoblastoma Treated with Intra-arterial Chemotherapy

Last Thursday O'Connell House hosted the book launch for 'After Ireland' authored by ND professor and esteemed academic of Irish Literature Declan Kiberd. Actor and founder of Field Day Stephen Rea was present to launch the book. Thank you to everyone who came out to support the launch and made the event a huge success!
It is an honor to have Marina Carr in house tonight to speak to our study abroad students about theatre in Ireland!

Every Tuesday we host guest speakers from various sectors of Irish society to come speak to the students. We were very appreciative to have Anne Kearney and Angela Mitchell come speak to the students a few weeks ago about Irish Education and how it differs from US Education!

God is moving!! The past couple days have been incredible. It's a small world and there have been moments where God is the only one that could make these occurrences happen. Just on Tuesday Night our flight from Munich to Paris got cancelled we were able to talk with European customer service and get on the next flight just an hour later on standby. We landed safely in Paris and took a bus to the station nearest our Hostel. We ended up running into a 25 year old man named Carlos who was from Yukatan and he was as lost as we were in such a new city. His friend he was meeting in Paris was a day late and he didn't have a place to stay. He ended up coming with us to our Hostel which was full and the owner of the hostel allowed him to sleep on the floor in our room. All day the next day he came with us to the Eiffel Tower and we shared stories we laughed and we didn't care about the language barrier or our life circumstances. For that moment we were One. He left that night as family and left us with a saying  Mi Casa es tu Casa   My house is your house . Later that night a young man named Anurug got to the Hostel but it was full and he pleaded for a spot the owner allowed him. I just started talking to him in the lobby and we conversed and talked about traveling experiences. He was from Tanzania. He ended up being by himself in Paris and We invited him to come along with us the next day to the Palace of Versailles. It was a beautiful day and again we shared stories and culture. He invited us to Tanzania and will continue to be a friend for a life time. It is these moments that we put differences aside to just be as God calls us to be One.

Bracing for impact. 🌊 But I actually did make this face as I stared in horror at my laptop last night. My site was being redirected to another site (NOT mine) after I made a few changes earlier in the day. The thought that I lost my travel writing and stories from the past four years was devastating. Thankfully Laviwashere.com is back up and running but it made me realize how truly intangible and virtual the Internet is. If I don’t print these photos and stories will I still have them in 50 years?

It’s not quite the same as the autumns I experienced in NYC and Madrid but I’ll take it. Weekend drives on the Pacific Coast Highway always make me feel like I’m seeing the Pacific Ocean for the first time.
I don’t get to see this view very often since I live in the Mission District. Whenever I make my way up here it always reminds me that I kind of love living in San Francisco.

Cinder Cone Volcano is surrounded by lava beds aptly named “Fantastic Lava Beds” 😂 and these unique rainbow-colored hills. Look at those colorful hills! The view from the top of Cinder Cone had me in awe seeing so many different landscapes in one 360-degree view.

I hope you scroll through to understand the whole picture. Cinder Cone Volcano looked like a massive pile of gravel until we got to the top. With every slippery step on the steep gravel we felt like we weren’t getting closer to the top. We didn’t expect to find the bowl-shaped crater in the middle which was once it’s volcanic vent. And a perfect view of Lassen Peak the volcano we hiked a day earlier. I’ve seen these other-worldly landscapes in Central and South America but never expected to see them in Northern California!

If you could have a house on the beach or in the mountains which would you choose? . The beaches of San Francisco are too cold for me so I’ve taken to the mountains when I go on weekend trips nearby. I’m much more of a mountain gal than I used to be but I still think I’d choose the beach. But where? Hmm...I’m going to take my imaginary fortune and think this over some more...💸

Never let anyone discredit or diminish your deepest thoughts feelings and personal hardships by simply categorizing them all into one painfully misconstrued word. If you do not understand why you feel certain things if you are having serious concerns about life or if you just need to talk to someone please call the number below. Whether or not you can feel or understand it at this very moment you are so loved. Even though you all come from completely different backgrounds live completely different lives and know completely different people you are loved appreciated and admired just the same. And all we can long for is that one day you see that for yourself and that you continue seeing it for others. 24/7/365 Crisis Hotline: (755) 784-8090 OR 1 (800) 273-8255 or text  ANSWER  to 839863 ••••• I've also included a portrait of Dorothea Dix one of the first (and one of my personal favorite) advocates of both modern mental healthcare & prison reform in the United States. Throughout most of her adult life Dorothea traveled throughout the United States & Europe researching and advocating for new humane well-funded mental institutions. By the time of her death she was directly  involved in founding 32 mental hospitals. This song relates to the type of person who does it all and keeps a smile on while doing it all. They put the pressure on themselves to never ask for help as their perfectionist nature doesn't allow them to. But all the while their lack of asking for assistance gets them into trouble as they now feel run down tired irritable and not being able to perform their best. The song takes a turn when it start to voice that “It’s ok to feel pain” and that “everybody needs help sometimes.” This song holds a special place in my heart because I am that person. Every time I sing this song it is a reminder that I need to let go of always striving to be “perfect” because “perfect” doesn’t exist. It is a reminder to accept and love myself imperfections and all.  What better way to challenge myself than to put out a live/ stripped down video. Voice cracks weird facial expressions and all. With that- I hope you all enjoy.  Special thanks to @markvogelmusic for accompanying me on this song and @kyledijamco for filming! :) <3  Link in bio

Moody skies in the Swiss Alps 😍💕 Switzerland has become one of my favorite places in the world.
Peering through the fall leaves and catching a glimpse of Mt. Pilatus emerging through the fog was one of the most beautiful things I've ever seen. Switzerland was such a dream 🇨🇭🏔🍂
Sometimes the simple moments are the most beautiful ✨. I took this photo while on a boat in Lucern Switzerland. There was a haze over the lake that made the surrounding mountains look so enchanting.

Watched the sky light up over the Alps on my last night in Switzerland 😍🏔 just in time for @alexborsuk's birthday. It was definitely hard to leave the next day after this!

This was an experience I will never forget--catching the last light on top of the Swiss Alps. It was one of those moments I almost couldn't believe was real. Standing at 10000 feet seeing miles and miles of mountain peaks stretched in the distance made me feel so small and insignificant in the best way possible.  Switzerland was hands down one of the most beautiful countries I've ever visited in my life. Thank you to @engelberg.titlis for making this experience possible 🏔💕#flyswissbacktonature

Having the opportunity to watch the sunset on top of a mountain in Switzerland was truly a once and a lifetime experience. Before traveling here I'll admit that Switzerland wasn't high on my bucket list but after experiencing its beauty for the first time last week it's now become one of my favorite destinations. Coupled with some of the best company I'm already planning my return trip 😍🏔🇨🇭

Seahorses are truly unique and not just because of their unusual equine shape. Unlike most other fish they are monogamous and mate for life. Rarer still they are among the only animal species on Earth in which the male bears the unborn young.  This video shows a female seahorse transferring eggs into the males pouch!! Not something you see everyday.. In the ocean the average seahorse can live 4-6 years but this time is normally shorter for those held in captivity due to stress and poor conditions. Although there are some records of them living up to 10 years in captivity..! What are your views on this guys? - Caught on video by @aqualush_info

Today is #worldmentalhealthday 1 in 5 Americans struggle with mental disorders each year and I am one of them. (*gasps* omg how could she share that on social media) Anxiety and depression can make life a whirlwind of confusion and emotional exhaustion. Somedays it makes you wake up and literally just say  NO.  It is absolutely nothing to be ashamed of you showed up today that counts. But for those of you who aren't around me on a daily basis or aren't more than acquaintances how would you know that I was dealing with anxiety regularly if I hadn't written this post? Exactly. Mental disorders occur in people of all colors shapes sizes religions political views ages and backgrounds. So let's end the stigma and start the conversations. No one should feel like they are experiencing the effects of mental disorders alone. Chances are there are a lot more people in your life than you might think who are dealing with these things on a day to day basis. So if there's anything you take away from this it's plz be kind to everyone you meet and always make taking good care of yourself a top priority!!! 🎉💕

This year for my 23rd birthday I wanted to do something special since I share the same birthday as both Mikey and Bridget. The Swifty Foundation began with Michael Gustafson who was diagnosed with brain cancer at the age of 10. Shortly after his diagnosis Michael began fundraising for cancer research and recruited his friends to help. At the end of his battle Mikey created the Swifty Foundation before his death at age 15 to raise awareness and funds for pediatric cancer research so that: “No other child will have to go through what I did.” So I would like to encourage my friends and family to help me to find a cure for pediatric brain cancer and donate to Swifty 100% of the donations go straight to pediatric cancer research. Sharing my birthday with both of them makes it even more special of a day. Donate on November 16th to help me help Mikey in his  master plan  💛  Also this Thanksgiving I will be running the Grant Park Turkey Trot 5k in support of Swifty and I wanted to run in memory of Mikey and help fundraise for a great foundation. ••LINK IN MY BIO•• #TogetherTowardsHope #swifty

We tend to fall into cyclic patterns of overthinking and self-criticizing that ruin our perception of life sometimes to the point of no longer wanting it. I've lost friends to suicide and almost lost many more the past few years. Suicide and suicide ideation are severe issues that often go unaddressed.  So let's go back to when we were little kids and we weren't afraid to ask for help when we needed it. Let's try to judge less both ourselves and others and breathe a little more deeply. Let go of the internship that you didn't get the test you bombed or the ass that didn't text you back.  Go ahead and scream cry punch a hole in the wall (security deposit tho) make pickle voodoo dolls like from Lilo & Stitch (personal fav) - whatever you need to do to get through it. Just don't hesitate to reach out. Don't ever give up on yourself. #WorldSuicidePreventionDay

4. Self. I sacrificed a lot for my dream of being a rocket scientist but as people around me earned summer jobs I was afraid. I feared I wasn't good enough and as I searched for something external to tell me I was I lost my identity. I started trying to fit the part:  What should I being doing?  Rather than  What do I want to do?  Recently a quote resonated with me: at the end of the day all we have is ourselves. No one can convince you of how amazing you are except yourself so take time for yourself do what you want and above all: love yourself. Your self expression might just put you the place you want to be. Trust me I'm a NASA engineer (intern). || Thank you to the people who have given me that advice for months: you were right but I wasn't ready to listen--you know who you are.

3. Brother. We weren't always good siblings but we figured it out. I couldn't be more thankful for the mutual respect we have for each other but I admire your respect of self. The best advice you ever gave me was simply  Do what you want.  At the end of the day you take life into your own hands make mistakes succeed fail but you always stay sure in yourself. Thank you for teaching me to love myself and above all: make my own luck. #nationalsiblingday

just because you're alone right now doesn't mean you're undateable. just because that pretty girl won't smile back at you doesn't mean you're undesirable. just because you haven't kissed a boy doesn't mean you're unattractive. stop blaming yourself for these things. love is one of those weird cosmic things that is simply beyond your control. you can try as hard as you like but really it'll only come to you when the time is right. stop thinking there is something wrong with YOU. there is absolutely NOTHING wrong with you. you are insanely attractive highly intelligent hella sweet and mad funny. stop discounting that. you are worth so so so much! i don't want you to forget that just because you haven't found  the one  yet.  the one  could be across the world at some random café reading your favorite book and drinking those chai lattes you love so much.  the one  could even be right next to you hoping you feel the same way as they feel about you.  the one  could be feeling just as alone as you do right now wishing they could just meet you already. and we'll never know where  the one  is at this moment and yeah that fucking sucks! hardcore!! but don't fret my dear. everything will fall into place soon. in the meantime fall in love with the wrong people. make mistakes. discover yourself. love yourself. THEN you'll be ready to settle down! but for now  the one  is yourself. we've all heard that quote about how important it is to love yourself before you open your heart to anyone else and even now as i type it i'm rolling my eyes so hard the retinas might detach but TRUST ME it is sooo true. i know you really want someone to hold at night when you feel like everything's crashing down and you want someone to share your giddy sunday brunches with but in the meantime why can't that someone be you? take care of yourself appreciate all that you are. xo

Happy Thanksgiving! There’s a lot to be thankful for this year. As my first full year not traveling full-time in a few years I think it makes me appreciate the adventures even more. • What are you thankful for this year? ✨
The more weekends we spend in the city the more I long to be out here in nature. With my favorite hiking partner. 🏔🌲

What’s your favorite season? Cold autumn days in San Francisco have me dreaming of warm sunny summer days in San Diego 🌞. Now looking at this photo I’m wondering why I wasn’t wearing a swimsuit and why I didn’t jump in! Come back summer!

It always throws me off a bit when we change the clocks back an hour but that’s nothing in comparison to having five hours of daylight when I visited Iceland in winter. What time do you think it is here: sunrise at 10am or sunset at 3pm?

Who’s going to Iceland this winter?! The days in winter are short but the natural beauty is like nothing else. • For those of you traveling to Iceland this winter I’ve included a blog post I wrote earlier this year with everything you need to know as you plan your trip. Link in bio! ❄️
Are we photobombing the volcano or is the volcano photobombing us? P.S. Isn’t it exciting when self-timer shots turn out well?🏔

Bracing for impact. 🌊 But I actually did make this face as I stared in horror at my laptop last night. My site was being redirected to another site (NOT mine) after I made a few changes earlier in the day. The thought that I lost my travel writing and stories from the past four years was devastating. Thankfully Laviwashere.com is back up and running but it made me realize how truly intangible and virtual the Internet is. If I don’t print these photos and stories will I still have them in 50 years?

It’s not quite the same as the autumns I experienced in NYC and Madrid but I’ll take it. Weekend drives on the Pacific Coast Highway always make me feel like I’m seeing the Pacific Ocean for the first time.
I don’t get to see this view very often since I live in the Mission District. Whenever I make my way up here it always reminds me that I kind of love living in San Francisco.

Cinder Cone Volcano is surrounded by lava beds aptly named “Fantastic Lava Beds” 😂 and these unique rainbow-colored hills. Look at those colorful hills! The view from the top of Cinder Cone had me in awe seeing so many different landscapes in one 360-degree view.

I hope you scroll through to understand the whole picture. Cinder Cone Volcano looked like a massive pile of gravel until we got to the top. With every slippery step on the steep gravel we felt like we weren’t getting closer to the top. We didn’t expect to find the bowl-shaped crater in the middle which was once it’s volcanic vent. And a perfect view of Lassen Peak the volcano we hiked a day earlier. I’ve seen these other-worldly landscapes in Central and South America but never expected to see them in Northern California!

If you could have a house on the beach or in the mountains which would you choose? . The beaches of San Francisco are too cold for me so I’ve taken to the mountains when I go on weekend trips nearby. I’m much more of a mountain gal than I used to be but I still think I’d choose the beach. But where? Hmm...I’m going to take my imaginary fortune and think this over some more...💸

Have you ever wondered who the face behind the Phi Mu LSU Instagram was? Well hello it’s me! My name is Madeline and I have loved serving as the Public Relations Chairman for Phi Mu Alpha Eta for the past year. If you had told me 2 years ago that I’d be serving on Phi Mu’s Executive Board I would have told you that you were crazy. I was the girl who went through rush unsure of whether or not being in a sorority was even right for her. But slowly I fell in love with this chapter. I fell in love with the people who made this place feel like home when mine was 300 miles away. I have learned that a sorority experience is what you make it. I made a decision to become involved in my chapter and because of that decision I have become a stronger leader and a better person. It has been an honor to serve this chapter and I will be forever grateful for this experience. #geauxphimu #4090isHФME

Our next #MeetExec post and #mucrushmonday goes to sweet Miss Peri Block! As this year's executive board wraps up their positions each of us has had time to reflect on what serving on exec has taught us. Here's what Peri had to say:  My favorite part about serving as Secretary on Phi Mu's Exec is having the unique opportunity to communicate with and get to know every single member of our chapter. The community and support I have found in Phi Mu is indescribable. Serving on the executive board has challenged me to not only become the best version of myself but to also put Phi Mu first. Serving as Secretary has been one of the most memorable experiences of my college career. I am so thankful for what Phi Mu has given me and I wouldn't trade this experience for the world. I also adore being called Secreperi and would like to be called that even when my term is over.  #Secreperi

Our next #MeetExec post goes to Treasurer Lindsey Berns! Here's her take on how serving on Exec had impacted her life.  I have absolutely loved being the treasurer for Phi Mu. It has been a humbling experience serving on the 2017 Exec and I can tell that I have grown as a person because of it. I have learned to budget time and money while also getting to know new people in my chapter. This opportunity to serve my chapter has been truly eye opening.  It has shown me that the girls of Phi Mu will support me in everything I do. My advice to any and all young women would be this: be the person you never thought you could be. Don't be afraid to take that leap because Phi Mu has your back. I love these girls and I love this chapter and the memories we have made will stick with me for forever.  #geauxphimu
